Abuja Emerald Lions Club in Conjunction with Abuja Central Lions Club, has planted over 50 trees in Abuja to help improve the environment, as part of its World Earth Day activities. The environmental project tag: “Keep Abuja Green and Fresh” was carried out yesterday along Maitama, Kubwa Expressway under the supervision of the deputy director of Parks and Recreation Centre. The chairperson of Abuja Emerald Club, Bridget Nwagbara, said that building a sustainable environment is one of the key service areas of the Lions Club internationally. “This is an initiative of the Abuja Emerald and Abuja Central Lions Club and it will be expanded to include the entire region. We planted 50 trees today to mark World Earth Day and we intend to plant 200 trees to mark World Environment Day hopefully in June this year. “Tree planting is important for environmental protection. Trees are crucial to the fight against global warming and climate change targeting Abuja Municipal Area Council,” she said. She also advised Nigerians on the need to always keep their environment clean and protected.